.TH "drm_dev_exit" 9 "drm_dev_exit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_dev_exit \- Exit device critical section
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_dev_exit
.BI "(int idx "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "idx" 12
index returned from \fBdrm_dev_enter\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function marks the end of a section that should not be entered after
the device has been unplugged.
